<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Garden Text Styling Example</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Georgia, serif;
      padding: 30px;
      background-color: #e6ffe6;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    .font-size {
      font-size: 22px;
    }

    .font-weight {
      font-weight: bold;
    }

    .font-style {
      font-style: italic;
    }

    .combined {
      font-size: 20px;
      font-weight: 600;
      font-style: oblique;
    }

    .section {
      background-color: #fff;
      padding: 20px;
      border-left: 8px solid #4CAF50;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <div class="section font-size">
    A garden is a place of peace and beauty. <br>
    This paragraph uses <strong>font-size: 22px</strong> to make it stand out gently.
  </div>

  <div class="section font-weight">
    A well-maintained garden can include colorful flowers, green grass, and shady trees. <br>
    This text uses <strong>font-weight: bold</strong> to emphasize its importance.
  </div>

  <div class="section font-style">
    Gardening is not just a hobby, it's a form of art and relaxation. <br>
    This text uses <strong>font-style: italic</strong> to add a softer, elegant touch.
  </div>

  <div class="section combined">
    With patience and care, any garden can flourish. <br>
    This sentence uses a combination of <strong>font-size</strong>, <strong>font-weight</strong>, and <strong>font-style</strong>.
  </div>

</body>
</html>
